   "id": "macro_dist_analysis",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2 Macronutrient Distribution Analysis\n",
    "Beyond raw calories, the **Acceptable Macronutrient Distribution Ranges (AMDR)** are critical for long-term health. We calculate the percentage of total energy derived from Protein, Fat, and Carbs to align our model with dietary balance guidelines:\n",
    "- **Protein:** 10-35% of daily calories\n",
    "- **Fat:** 20-35% of daily calories\n",
    "- **Carbs:** 45-65% of daily calories"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "feature_engineering",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-02-22T12:28:16.900343Z",
     "start_time": "2026-02-22T12:28:16.875320Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Feature Engineering: Macronutrient Percentages\n",
    "df['total_ener'] = (df['total_protein'] * 4) + (df['total_carbs'] * 4) + (df['total_fat'] * 9)\n",
    "df['p_pct'] = (df['total_protein'] * 4) / df['total_ener'].replace(0, 1)\n",
    "df['f_pct'] = (df['total_fat'] * 9) / df['total_ener'].replace(0, 1)\n",
    "df['c_pct'] = (df['total_carbs'] * 4) / df['total_ener'].replace(0, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "df[['p_pct', 'f_pct', 'c_pct']].describe()"
   ],
