   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ac2fa4a7d7c7e041",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.3 The Health Score Heuristic\n",
    "To provide a ground truth for the model, we define a **synthetic heuristic** based on WHO and AMDR guidelines:\n",
    "- **Base Score:** 9.0\n",
    "- **Penalties:** Excessive fat (>40% kcal), low protein (<12% kcal), high sugar (>60g), high sodium (>4000mg), and high calorie surplus.\n",
    "- **Rewards:** High fiber (>30g).\n",
    "- **Stochasticity:** +/- 0.3 random variance to simulate real-world logging noise."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c231a250ee36de5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.4 Density-Based Feature Engineering\n",
    "Raw gram counts can be biased by total caloric volume. To improve regression stability, we engineer **nutrient density** features (amount per 1000 kcal)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "e4b4923b6d9b041b",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-02-22T12:28:17.064170Z",
     "start_time": "2026-02-22T12:28:17.041243Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Engineering V2: Density Features\n",
    "df['fiber_density'] = (df['fiber'] * 1000) / df['total_calories'].replace(0, 1)\n",
    "df['sugar_density'] = (df['sugar'] * 1000) / df['total_calories'].replace(0, 1)\n",
    "df['sodium_density'] = (df['sodium'] * 1000) / df['total_calories'].replace(0, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "df[['fiber_density', 'sugar_density', 'sodium_density']].describe()"
   ],
